\b\fs36 OAuth authentication
\b0\fs24 \
\
It manages the access tokens by itself and save them to the user defaults.\
The authentication is mainly defined in the client's parent class: DDSocialNetworkClient. However, you do not have to worry about this class since the\
authentication is done by itself and you have nothing to do (the login page is automatically displayed when needed).\
Simply implement the methods in the DDSocialNetworkClient protocol, 2 of them being required:\
\
