- (\cf4 UIViewController\cf0  *)rootViewControllerForDisplayingLoginDialogForSocialMediaClient:(\cf3 DDSocialNetworkClient\cf0  *)client ;
\f0\fs24 \CocoaLigature1 \
\
Before ever displaying a login dialog, the client will ask your permission by asking its delegate.\
In this method you can handle stuff in case the login dialog shoud interrupt a game for example.\
You are free to return NO if you do not want the login window to interrupt. In the case, the login will simply fail and your delegate will be averted of it.\
\
You also have to return a UIViewController where the login dialog should be attached as a modal view controller.\
You should return a UIViewController which view is full-screen.\
\
