In order to support a client, simply instantiate an object from the class corresponding to your client.\
By looking at the header file, you will find a list of methods that you can call to post/request data to/from the client.\
\
There is also a protocol that your object can adopt. These delegate methods will be very useful and give a lot of information\
about the status of your posts/requests. In case you request data from a client, since the requests are asynchronous, the received data will\
be sent back to the delegate through these methods.\
\
